  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. In the United States, the primary anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement customer identification programs\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain records of financial activities\n4. Conduct due diligence on customers\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution. Internationally, organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) work to establish global standards for combating money laundering.",
